title: Millburn High School girls volleyball team wins tourney opener
text:
Millburn High School girls volleyball team wins tourney opener October 16, 2015 Last updated: Friday, October 16, 2015, 5:33 PM The Item of Millburn and Short Hills Print 
Millburn High School's varsity girls volleyball team has advanced to the first round of the Essex County Tournament. 
The 15th-seeded Millers moved on with a 25-16, 25-19 defeat of 18th-seeded North 13th Street Tech this afternoon in a county tourney preliminary round match at Millburn High School. 
The local spikers overcame a 12-5 second set deficit on their way to beating North 13th Street Tech for the second time this season. 
Millburn will face second-seeded Montclair Kimberley Academy, the holder of a preliminary round bye, Saturday, Oct. 24, in a first round match in Montclair. 
See the Thursday, Oct. 22, 2015 edition of The Item of Millburn and Short Hills for more details.
